Jayson Tatum scores 24 points, Terry Rozier adds 18 with seven rebounds as Boston takes Game 3 in overtime, 101-98.
LeBron James scores 38 points with seven assists, six rebounds, three steals and the game-winning basket to seal the Game 3 win for Cleveland, 105-103.
Kevin Durant posts 38 points and grabs nine rebounds as the Warriors take Game 4 and defeat the Pelicans 118-92.
Items.vs: New Orleans Pelicans vs. Golden State Warriors

Items.description: Chris Paul celebrates his birthday by leading all scorers with 27 points and 12 rebounds as the Rockets get the 100-87 win over the Jazz and take Game 4.
Dario Saric scores 25 points and eight rebounds while TJ McConnell gets the start and notches a career-high 19 points as the Sixers get their first win of the series and defeat the Celtics 103-92.
LeBron James posts 29 points, 8 rebounds, and 11 assists to help the Cavaliers sweep the series and defeat the Raptors 128-93.

Items.altTitle: Paul: 41 pts, 10 ast (reaches first Conf. finals)
Items.description: The Houston Rockets defeat the Utah Jazz 112-102 and are headed to the Western Conference Finals as Chris Paul notches a playoff career-high 41 points and dishes out 10 assists.

Items.altTitle: Curry: 28 pts; GSW into 4th straight West finals
Items.description: Steph Curry puts up 28 points and dishes out eight assists as the Warriors defeat the Pelicans 113-104 and advance to the Western Conference Finals.

Items.altTitle: Late rally sends Celtics to East finals
Items.description: Jayson Tatum scores 25 points, Jaylen Brown adds 24 as the Celtics take Game 5, 114-112 and advance to the Eastern Conference Finals.

Items.altTitle: Brown scores 23 points; LeBron held to 15
Items.description: Jaylen Brown puts up 23 points and grabs eight rebounds as the Celtics get the 10 win over the Cavaliers to take Game 1 of the Eastern Conference Finals.
Kevin Durant leads the Warriors to a 119-106 Game 1 win over the Rockets with 37 points and three rebounds.

Items.altTitle: Celtics outscore Cavs 71-47 after LeBron injury
Items.description: Jaylen Brown scores 23 points to lead a balanced Celtics attack over LeBron James' 42-point triple-double as the Celtics take Game 2, 107-94.
